{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place carrots in mixing bowl then grate <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place dates, apricots, apple sauce, maple syrup and vanilla extract in mixing bowl then chop <b>6 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add oats, coconut flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and reserved grated carrot then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>10 sec\/speed 3<b>.","Place desiccated coconut in a bowl. Take heaped tablespoons of mixture, form into 12 balls then roll in coconut until covered.","Serve or store in fridge in an airtight container for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 - 120 g carrots, cut in pieces (2 cm)","3 medjool dates, pitted, halved","4 dried apricots, pitted","2 Tbsp apple sauce (unsweetened)","2 Tbsp maple syrup","1 tsp vanilla extract","80 g rolled oats","30 g coconut flour","½ tsp ground cinnamon","¼ tsp ground nutmeg","¼ tsp ground ginger","10 - 20 g desiccated coconut, for rolling"]}],"id":"r316264","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-2CzTG8F5a-k\/XZapuax8ilI\/AAAAAAAAhUI\/YialgPbkXrkQQhxgGsTjQ465natBWsWtACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7BH7PrHGnK1q2w67.png","title":"Carrot Cake Energy Balls","publishedAt":"2018-04-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.5 g","fat":"1.5 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"11.7 g","calories":"305 kJ \/ 72 kcal"},"usefulItems":"airtight container, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Light and fluffy, these energy-laden balls have all the elements of a carrot cake wrapped up in a tasty ball! For additional protein, a scoop of protein powder could be added instead of the coconut flour. A delicious pre or post run snack, which non-runners would enjoy as well!"],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","15m","12 pieces"]}